item.description:
@BAsh_CntLgn wrote:

frank_:

its not a freaking buffer!!!111111111111

Thats true in that some arguments have to be there since they are crucial to the running of the game. However they can still add an arbitrary number of variables and mix them up as dummy arguments.

If you where to hook the arguments I recommend you check to make sure the arguments that are needed are there and all the rest are dummy. You could check this by making sure they where all of primitive types (not object/arrays) and the number of them was less than or equal to 3.
